Jinja2 is a templating language used to create dynamic templates for web applications. Here are the four conditional statements used in Jinja2:

1. `{% if %}` - This is the most basic conditional statement in Jinja2. It is used to display a block of code only if the specified condition is true.

Example:
```python
{% if user.is_authenticated %}
    <p>Welcome, {{ user.username }}!</p>
{% endif %}
```
2. `{% ifnot %}` - This conditional statement is similar to `{% if %}` but displays the block of code only if the condition is false.

Example:
```python
{% ifnot user.is_authenticated %}
    <p>Please log in to access this page.</p>
{% endif %}
```
3. `{% elif %}` - This conditional statement allows you to check multiple conditions at once. It is used in combination with the `{% if %}` and `{% elif %}` statements.

Example:
```python
{% if user.is_authenticated %}
    <p>Welcome, {{ user.username }}!</p>
{% elif user.is_admin %}
    <p>Welcome, administrator!</p>
{% else %}
    <p>Welcome, guest!</p>
{% endif %}
```
4. `{% endif %}` - This statement is used to close the `{% if %}` statement and complete the conditional block.

Example:
```python
{% if user.is_authenticated %}
    <p>Welcome, {{ user.username }}!</p>
{% endif %}
```

