The function first initializes a temporary array `` sum `` to store the intermediate results. It then iterates over the rows and columns of the matrix `` A ``, and for each element `` a_ik ``, it computes the product of `` a_ik `` with each element `` b_jk `` of matrix `` B ``. It then computes the determinant of the matrix `` A `` by multiplying `` a_ik `` with `` b_jk ``, and stores the result in the `` sum `` array.

The function then adds the contents of the `` sum `` array to the `` C `` array to obtain the final result. It does this by incrementing the `` lane `` variable after each iteration, which is used to optimize the vector load instructions. This ensures that the `` C `` array is updated with the correct values for each iteration of the loop.

Note that this is just an example implementation, and there may be more efficient ways to perform matrix multiplication using AVX-512.

