Here is a simple PowerShell function that calculates the GCD (Greatest Common Divisor) of two numbers:
```sql
function Get-GCD {
    param(
        [int]$number1,
        [int]$number2
    )

    $result = 1

    if ($number1 -gt $number2) {
        $temp = $number1
        $number1 = $number2
        $number2 = $temp
    }

    while ($number1 -gt 0) {
        if ($number2 == 0) {
            $result = $number1
        } else {
            $result = $number2
        }
        $number1 = $number1 - $number2
        $number2 = $number2 - $number1
    }

    return $result
}
```
To use this function, simply call it with the two numbers you want to find the GCD of, like this:
```sql
$gcd = Get-GCD -number1 10 -number2 15
```
This will return the GCD of 10 and 15, which is 5.

